<!-- SC_OFF --><div class="md"><p>So for context, I was playing with a friend and he had put me in stalemate and then when he noticed that he reached over the board and knocked over my king. And said &quot;I just like to do it.&quot; I personally found that disrespectful but I&#39;m not sure if it&#39;s generally frowned upon.</p> </div><!-- SC_ON --> &#32; submitted by &#32; <a href="https://www.reddit.com/user/Mysterious185"> /u/Mysterious185 </a> <br/> <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/chess/comments/13jagtp/is_it_disrespectful_to_knock_over_the_opponents/">[link]</a></span> &#32; <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/chess/comments/13jagtp/is_it_disrespectful_to_knock_over_the_opponents/">[comments]</a></span>